<BaseLayout title="One-sentence Ledger" description="A natural-language expense and split-bill tool." lang="en" path="projects" switchTo="/projects/one-sentence-ledger/">
  <article class="prose">
    <div class="eyebrow">Project / Prototype</div>
    <h1>One-sentence Ledger</h1>
    <p class="lead">A natural-language expense and split-bill tool designed to make daily financial records lighter, faster, and easier to review.</p>

    <h2>Problem</h2>
    <p>Most expense apps ask users to tap through too many fields. The real problem is not that people cannot track spending. It is that the cost of recording is too high.</p>

    <h2>Core Idea</h2>
    <p>The user writes one sentence, such as “Dinner with A and B cost 180 yesterday, I paid first.” The system extracts amount, time, participants, payer, and split logic.</p>

    <h2>Stack</h2>
    <div class="tags">
      <span class="tag">AI</span>
      <span class="tag">Natural language</span>
      <span class="tag">Personal finance</span>
      <span class="tag">Small tools</span>
    </div>

    <h2>Status</h2>
    <p>Prototype. The first goal is to validate natural-language input, structured parsing, and split-bill logic before adding export, charts, or long-term review.</p>

    <p><a href="/en/projects/">← Back to projects</a></p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
